==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: morpheme
<hw>mor"pheme</hw> <pr>(m⟦ocir⟧r"f⟦emac⟧m)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Linguistics)</fld> <def>The smallest unit of meaning of a
language, which cannot be divided into smaller parts carrying meaning;
it is usually smaller than a single wordform, such as the
<examp>-ed</examp> morpheme of verbs in the past tense or the
<examp>-s</examp> morpheme of nouns in the plural form.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>morphemic</ent>⟦br⟧
